Inter Milan May Try to Sign Tottenham’s Luka Modric: Soccer Roundup

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-04-21T10:00:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/inter-milan-may-try-to-sign-tottenham-s-luka-modric-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of
soccer stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the
Web.  Modric for Inter?  Inter Milan will try to sign Luka Modric this summer if
Tottenham doesn’t qualify for the Champions League, the  Daily
Mirror  reported.  The Italian champion wants to rebuild its squad and sees
Modric as one of the best midfielders in  Europe , the Mirror
added.  Race for Tevez  Juventus may challenge Inter Milan in trying to sign  Carlos Tevez  if Manchester City allows the Argentine to leave, the
 Daily Telegraph  reported.  Tevez is expected to quit City at the end of this season,
the newspaper added.  Sevilla Wants Berbatov  Manchester United striker Dimitar Berbatov is being
targeted by Sevilla,  the Sun  reported.  The Bulgarian’s contract runs out next year and the
Spaniards hope to recruit him for a “cut-price”  12 million
pounds ($20 million), the newspaper added.  Russians Return?  Rubin Kazan may take Tottenham’s Roman Pavlyuchenko and
Diniyar Bilyaletdinov of Everton back to Russia in the
offseason, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Rubin manager Kurban Berdyev is keen to make “big moves”
when the Russian transfer window opens in August, the Mail
added.  Blues’  Madrid  Target  Chelsea is poised to make a move for Real Madrid’s teenage
striker Alvaro Morata, according to the  Daily Mirror .  Blues owners Roman Abramovich’s scouts believe the 18-year-
old may have a 10 million-pound buyout clause in his contract,
the Mirror added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in  London  at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
